    <a title="Erwin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21812440-erwin"><img alt="Erwin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521018362p2/21812440.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/677090875?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erwin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erwin" href="/user/show/21812440-erwin">Erwin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780571230570" href="/book/show/819779.Such_a_Long_Journey">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21812440-erwin?shelf=indian-authors">indian-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21812440-erwin?shelf=man-booker-long-short-list">man-booker-long-short-list</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer677090875" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1474688446339414745">I really enjoyed this book. It is a touching story of an Indian family in the early seventies, a turbulent time in India&apos;s history. Mistry managed to create a colourful and rich setting and his characters are well believable, imperfect and therefore very human.<br/> I gave it four stars because it did not drag me into the story like his other novel A Fine Balance did. I still felt I was kept at a comfortable distance where in AFB I, as a reader, felt I was being made a part of the misery and happines</span>
  <span id="freeText1474688446339414745" style="display:none">I really enjoyed this book. It is a touching story of an Indian family in the early seventies, a turbulent time in India's history. Mistry managed to create a colourful and rich setting and his characters are well believable, imperfect and therefore very human.<br /> I gave it four stars because it did not drag me into the story like his other novel A Fine Balance did. I still felt I was kept at a comfortable distance where in AFB I, as a reader, felt I was being made a part of the misery and happiness of the main characters. <br />Yet it is a remarkable debut novel (he did write a collection of short stories before this, which I recommend too). Read this novel first (if you still can) and know that his work gets even better than this. Next stop: Family Matters! <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1474688446339414745" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

