  <span id="freeText9498253750984628975" style="display:none">What a lovely book ! The protagonist is a regular guy, a typical Indian father, and he wins you over with his gentleness and approach to life. The story is set against backdrop of Mumbai and the turbulent times during 1971 war. Politics of that decade makes a sneak peek appearance, yet is always influencing the background story. The characters you thought you wouldn’t like, also grow on you, much like life itself. The major events unravel slowly, but the story moves fast. Most characters are well etched, their stories receive their due as the book progresses. Is there a happy ending? Yes and No, with such books, you always have a feeling that the story should continue, especially when it ends with a crescendo.. </span>
