  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_128137138" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/128137138" />
    <a title="Preetha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1494083-preetha"><img alt="Preetha" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/128137138?book_show_action=true">Oct 27, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Preetha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Preetha" href="/user/show/1494083-preetha">Preetha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer128137138" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4226991558012896194">Adorable , heartbreaking and enduring ! The soul of the book remained with me long after I finished reading it. Almost as if I had just met the people in the story and travelled a part of their journey with them ! That’s how beautifully Rohinton Mistry has etched out his characters in this heart rendering tale of relationships, love , betrayal and pain. The book tells us the story of Gustad Noble , a simple and honest man, one who remains immaterial and inconsequential in the larger scheme of so</span>
  <span id="freeText4226991558012896194" style="display:none">Adorable , heartbreaking and enduring ! The soul of the book remained with me long after I finished reading it. Almost as if I had just met the people in the story and travelled a part of their journey with them ! That’s how beautifully Rohinton Mistry has etched out his characters in this heart rendering tale of relationships, love , betrayal and pain. The book tells us the story of Gustad Noble , a simple and honest man, one who remains immaterial and inconsequential in the larger scheme of society's design, who like any other ordinary person does not demand much out of life, other than health and happiness for his family and a better future for his children. He believes that his struggles have been rewarded when his son gets through the IIT entrance exam. Faced with his son’s refusal to follow the dream that his father has nurtured for him, Gustad bitterly examines his life gone by, his trials and challenges, the sacrifices that he endures for his family and friends , which he feels has all added upto nothing. Set against the backdrop of the political climate during the Indo-China war in 1964 and the Indo-Pak war in 1971, Gustad’s resilience and strength of character is put to test when he helplessly witnesses the death of his best friend whose life is eaten away by the corruption that rules the corridors of political power ; and his otherwise uneventful life is dragged into murky and threatening situations , led by the loyalties he harbours and stands by. The display of crankiness and superstitions at Khodadad building and the light hearted Dinshawji who laughs his way out of life (not into shiv sena’s hearts though), provide a sprinkling of humour to the story. The character that stood out for me though was that of Tehmul , who provides a kind of fragility and sensitivity to life that almost breaks your heart and makes you feel partly responsible for the shameful way in which society ‘accommodates and tolerates ‘ and even exploits a person with his challenges. All in all through his characters , Rohinton Mistry reminds us or even teaches us a thing or two about friendships, loyalties and relationships and leaves you thinking about and questioning yourself on what really matters at the end of it all !</span>
  <a data-text-id="4226991558012896194" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

